  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wouldn't know that, because there was-- where my father went was Gerrer shtiebel.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then there was Mizrahi, where my uncle, belonged to Mizrahi.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There is a difference in the degree of how religious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Gerrer Hasid is one which only follows the Gerrer rabbi.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Gerrer rabbi was a real Hasid.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mizrahi was a bit more modern.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, the Mizrahi-- my uncle already had a short beard cut.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was more modern.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we knew my father was a Gerrer Hasid.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Shabbat, for instance, after he went to synagogue and then came home-- especially after lunch-- there is always the three meals, you know, [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in between my father would always have this enormous, wonderful, you know, the [INAUDIBLE], [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the mishnah.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had enormous books.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he would start always reading a portion from it, Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was mainly what he would do on a Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The family was coming together, the children, the cousins.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
